{
  "answer": "**The specific moment occurs after Andrew's first public scourging by the Mermedonians, when he is led to prison at evening.**[^1]\n\nThis follows his capture: an immense war-band binds his hands and drags him through the city streets, scourging him all day until sunset, after which \"The people then led their loathed enemy to the prison.\"[^2] He remains there overnight amid harsh winter weather, praising God, until guards lead him out the next morning for further torments.[^3] (Note: He is led to/from prison repeatedly during his ordeal.)\n\n[^1]: Cynewulf, *Andreas*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-5d78fc).\n[^2]: Cynewulf, *Andreas*, [paragraphs](/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-34b202:p-5d78fc).\n[^3]: Cynewulf, *Andreas*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-5d78fc).",
